	in the region with the strong toroidal magnetic field is made of
	welded-together tubular &ldquo;bellows&rdquo; of different diameters.
	For this reason the chamber has a high electrical resistance for
	currents flowing in the poloidal direction. Owing to the high electrical
	resistance of the new chamber and the considerably larger margin
	of mechanical strength, discharges can be obtained in a toroidal
