	is discussed. The same mechanism might be responsible for the positive
	potential spikes during a saw-tooth crash, also observed using HIBP.
	Another phenomenon observed using HIBP was quasi-coherent potential
	oscillations with the frequency close to one of the GAM. Possible
	location of these oscillations in the core region r / a ? 0.33 is
	discussed.},
