  abstract = {The present report is devoted to investigation of plasma turbulence
	behaviour during a transition to the improved confinement triggered
	by RF power launching in the limiter discharges of the TUMAN-3M and
	the FT-2 tokamaks. The experiments have been carried out with using
	of the Doppler reflectometry based on backscattering with oblique
	incidence of probing microwave beam, for which in plasma there is
	a cutoff. The observation of the Doppler frequency shift of scattering
	spectra in such an experiment allows to estimate the plasma fluctuation
	poloidal velocity in tokamak. A specific transition to improved confinement
	initiated by RF pulse was revealed in the TUMAN-3M tokamak during
	ICR heating. The drastic narrowing of backscattering spectra associated
	with the transport suppression has been observed. The experiment
	in the FT-2 tokamak has been performed during the transition to H-mode
	triggered by the RF pulse of the lower-hybrid frequency region. The
	strong shear of plasma rotation observed via Doppler reflectometry
	strictly corresponded to appearance of the improved confinement.
