	response outside the transition, separate criteria on the plasma
	and halo Lundquist values are required. For the benchmarked equilibria
	the critical Lundquist values are 10<sup>8</sup> and 10<sup>3</sup>
	for the ideal-like and halo regions, respectively. Notably, this
	gives a ratio on the order of 10<sup>5</sup>, which is much larger
	than experimentally measured values using T<sub>e</sub> values associated
	with the top of the pedestal and separatrix. Excellent agreement
	with ELITE and GATO calculations are made when sharp boundary transitions
	in the resistivity are used and a small amount of physical dissipation
	is added for conditions very near and below marginal ideal stability.},
