  volume    = {17},
  abstract  = {Plasma relaxation inside a highly conducting cylindrical boundary
	is studied both experimentally and computationally. Dynamics are
	initiated by the introduction of two equal helicity spheromaks at
	either end of the cylinder. In the experiment, dense, high-magnetic-flux
	spheromaks are injected into the flux conserving volume with magnetized
