	sufficient to alter the stability of the marginal state. There is
	a slight delay in the response of energy exchanged among fluctuations,
	which reduces the m=0 fluctuations. Loss of dynamo effect as fluctuation
	amplitudes decrease leads to nonlocal pulse penetration that enhances
