  volume    = {103},
  abstract  = {For pt.I see ibid., vol.102, no.A11, p.24183-93 (1997). Magnetic clouds
	are commonly modeled as flux ropes and, less frequently, as spheromaks
	or toroids. In this second paper on propagating spheromaks the authors
	study the interaction of their initial internal field (depending
