	axis (evolving into the toroid's hole) to be aligned with the radial
	direction irrespective of its initial orientation. This means that
	a hypothetical spacecraft can cross the resulting toroid only once,
	thereby observing signatures similar to a flux rope crossing. Double
	crossings are excluded even near the Sun (0.3 AU). Therefore the
