	would give the impression of a roughly axisymmetric spheromak, the
	instantaneous current structure does not. Hundred per cent variations
	in J measured at the magnetic axis can be explained by the rotation
	of a current filament that has a width equal to half of the radius
	of the flux-conserving first wall. In positive gun operation, current
	leaves the filament in the confinement region leading to high wall
	current there. In negative gun operation, wall current remains low
