	and time-scale, and in dimensionality. We are developing algorithms
	for coupling such processes in a manner that allows each to be advanced
	on the relevant time-scale. In particular, the goal is to advance
	the transport equations with a time-step on the order of the energy
	confinement time. Our methods are being tested by developing a prototype
	simulation code, CORSICA. This code is being constructed by taking
	existing codes and coupling them together as modules in a single
	code. The three main focuses of the project are: (1) coupling a 1-D
	core transport code to an axisymmetric free-boundary MHD equilibrium
	code (LLNL's TEQ) and to circuit equations for the poloidal field
	coils and passive structure (the resulting 1-1/2 D transport code
	is known as CORSICA 1.0); (2) coupling the core transport code to
	a 2-D edge transport code (UEDGE); and (3) coupling the transport
